    'faq.sub':'Have questions? Here are answers to the most common questions from our patients.',
    'faq.q1':'Is cosmetic surgery in Tunisia safe?',
    'faq.a1':'Absolutely. Tunisia is one of the most recognised medical tourism destinations in the world. Our partner clinics are ISO 9001 certified, regularly audited, and our surgeons are trained at the best European universities.',
    'faq.q2':'How does an initial consultation work?',
    'faq.a2':'The first consultation takes place via video conference with one of our medical coordinators. You present your expectations, send your photos and receive a personalised quote within 48h.',
    'faq.q3':'How long should I plan for my stay?',
    'faq.a3':'The duration varies depending on the procedure. For facial surgery (rhinoplasty, facelift), plan a minimum of 7 to 10 days. For body procedures (liposuction, abdominoplasty), 10 to 14 days.',
    'faq.q4':'Do the prices really include everything?',
    'faq.a4':'Yes, our packages are 100% transparent. The quote includes: surgeon fees, anaesthesia costs, clinic stay, post-operative medication, transfers, accommodation and flight. There are no hidden fees.',
    'faq.q5':'How do I pay? Is a deposit required?',
    'faq.a5':'A 20% deposit is required at booking to secure your surgical date. The balance is payable upon your arrival in Tunisia. We accept SEPA transfers, Visa/Mastercard cards and cash in EUR/TND.',
